Step 1: Set Up Identity

Install Packages:

Ensure you have the necessary NuGet packages installed. Add the following packages if they are not already installed:

        dotnet add package Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity.EntityFrameworkCore
dotnet add package Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity.UI
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design


    Add Identity Services in Program.cs:

Create User Model: 

If you want to add custom properties to the default Identity User.

Configure Services: Add Identity services in your Startup.cs or Program.cs.

Create Account Controllers and Views: For login, registration, and logout.

Configure Authentication and Authorization: Ensure your application knows how to handle authenticated users.
